            <person xml:id="pers1026">
               <p>One of four sons of Capt. <persName><ref target="/persons/pers1021.xml"/>James
                     Hitchens</persName> of <placeName>Gwennap</placeName>, William served as an
                     <seg ana="itinerancy">itinerant</seg> minister from about <date from="1745"
                     to="1758">1745–58</date> (see <hi rend="italic">Works</hi>, 10:260, 286). In
                     <date when="1757">1757</date> he was briefly forced into military service. He
                  subsequently married and settled in <placeName>Bristol</placeName> as a hatter,
                  serving many years as a local preacher. See Atmore, <hi rend="italic"
                     >Memorial</hi>, 190–91.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
